---
description: Backend API workspace conventions for Node/TypeScript changes
globs: apps/api/**/*.ts
alwaysApply: false
---

# API Backend Rule

- Keep API/domain logic in `apps/api`; avoid coupling to `apps/web`.
- Enforce authz checks on protected operations and preserve security boundaries.
- Prefer deterministic unit/integration tests for changed behavior.
- For bug fixes, include a regression test that fails before and passes after.
- Keep shared schemas/types in `packages/shared` when consumed by multiple apps.
- Do not relax coverage gates without explicit owner + expiry in PR notes.
